Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive migration plan.

---

# CitedBy.ai: Vite SPA to Next.js App Router Migration Plan

## Table of Contents
1. [Route Structure](#1-route-structure)
2. [State Management Migration](#2-state-management-migration)
3. [Layout Architecture](#3-layout-architecture)
4. [API Routes for AI Services](#4-api-routes-for-ai-services)
5. [Component Migration](#5-component-migration)
6. [Config Changes](#6-config-changes)
7. [Testing Strategy](#7-testing-strategy)
8. [Execution Order](#8-execution-order)

---

## 1. Route Structure

### Critical Decision: Flatten the /app prefix

The existing Next.js app nests authenticated routes at `app/(app)/app/*`, creating URLs like `/app/projects`. This is redundant. The migration should flatten to remove the `/app` prefix, making routes like `/projects`, `/dashboard`, `/tools/smc-studio`.

### Directory Naming Conflict

**The `pages/` directory MUST be renamed** before migration. Next.js interprets a root `pages/` directory as the Pages Router, which conflicts with the App Router. Move all 36 SPA page components to `lib/views/`.

### Complete Route Map

| # | Old ViewName | Next.js URL Path | App Router File |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `home` (logged out) | `/` | `app/(public)/page.tsx` |
| 2 | `login` | `/login` | `app/(auth)/login/page.tsx` |
| 3 | `home` (logged in) | `/` (redirect to `/dashboard`) | middleware redirect |
| 4 | `dashboard` | `/dashboard` | `app/(app)/dashboard/page.tsx` |
| 5 | `analyze` | `/analyze` | `app/(app)/analyze/page.tsx` |
| 6 | `projects` | `/projects` | `app/(app)/projects/page.tsx` |
| 7 | `results` | `/results` | `app/(app)/results/page.tsx` |
| 8 | `history` | `/history` | `app/(app)/history/page.tsx` |
| 9 | `ai-monitoring` | `/monitoring/ai` | `app/(app)/monitoring/ai/page.tsx` |
| 10 | `alerts` | `/monitoring/alerts` | `app/(app)/monitoring/alerts/page.tsx` |
| 11 | `bot-tracking` | `/monitoring/bot-tracking` | `app/(app)/monitoring/bot-tracking/page.tsx` |
| 12 | `reputation` | `/monitoring/reputation` | `app/(app)/monitoring/reputation/page.tsx` |
| 13 | `citation-dashboard` | `/citations` | `app/(app)/citations/page.tsx` |
| 14 | `tracked-queries` | `/citations/tracked-queries` | `app/(app)/citations/tracked-queries/page.tsx` |
| 15 | `citation-detail` | `/citations/detail` | `app/(app)/citations/detail/page.tsx` |
| 16 | `benchmark` | `/citations/benchmark` | `app/(app)/citations/benchmark/page.tsx` |
| 17 | `v3-alerts` | `/citations/alerts` | `app/(app)/citations/alerts/page.tsx` |
| 18 | `alert-settings` | `/citations/alert-settings` | `app/(app)/citations/alert-settings/page.tsx` |
| 19 | `monthly-report` | `/citations/monthly-report` | `app/(app)/citations/monthly-report/page.tsx` |
| 20 | `calibration` | `/citations/calibration` | `app/(app)/citations/calibration/page.tsx` |
| 21 | `generative-tools` | `/tools` | `app/(app)/tools/page.tsx` |
| 22 | `smc-studio` | `/tools/smc-studio` | `app/(app)/tools/smc-studio/page.tsx` |
